oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tally-Ho 1955
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Florida State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This edition was dedicated to Manly Whitcomb. Burt "Buddy" Reynolds had his best season as a left halfback on the Florida State University football team during his freshman year in 1954. A knee injury forced him from the lineup in mid-season, but he was healthy enough to make an appearance in the Sun Bowl against Texas Western University on January 1, 1955. After that, chronic knee problems ended his promising football career. Reynolds went on to become one of the most successful actors in movie box office history.

oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tally-Ho 1971
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Florida State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The 1971 Florida State University Tally Ho featured the editorial cartoons of Doug Marlette, and was not in the traditional yearbook format. This edition had no student portraits, was topical and stylish, and served more as a pamphlet for student causes. The annual publication was discontinued after this edition, along with the student publications department. Marlette attended Florida State University from 1969 to 1971, but stopped six hours short of a degree to become the editorial cartoonist for the Charlotte Observer. He would become best known for his Kudzu comic strip. Marlette died in 2007 at the age of 57.

oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Florida State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Tallahassee native and Florida State University freshman Faye Dunaway was on the 1958 Miss FSU Court (page 146), was active in drama, and a member of Pi Beta Phi sorority.
